#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="mn97"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "mn97:0.1"
msgid "Majjhima Nikāya 97 "
msgstr "Middle Discourses 97 "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "mn97:0.2"
msgid "Dhanañjānisutta "
msgstr "With Dhanañjāni "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p><span class="evam">
#. REF: nya1, pts-vp-pli2.185, sc1
msgctxt "mn97:1.1"
msgid "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—"
msgstr "So I have heard. "

#. HTML: </span>
msgctxt "mn97:1.2"
msgid "ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā rājagahe viharati veḷuvane kalandakanivāpe. "
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying near Rājagaha, in the Bamboo Grove, the squirrels’ feeding ground. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya2
msgctxt "mn97:2.1"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena āyasmā sāriputto dakkhiṇāgirismiṃ cārikaṃ carati mahatā bhikkhusaṃghena saddhiṃ. "
msgstr "Now at that time Venerable Sāriputta was wandering in the Southern Hills together with a large Saṅgha of mendicants. "

#. VAR: vassaṃvuṭṭho → vassaṃ vuttho (bj, s1-3, km)
msgctxt "mn97:2.2"
msgid "Atha kho aññataro bhikkhu rājagahe vassaṃvuṭṭho yena dakkhiṇāgiri yenāyasmā sāriputto tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā āyasmatā sāriputtena saddhiṃ sammodi. "
msgstr "Then a certain mendicant who had completed the rainy season residence in Rājagaha went to the Southern Hills, where he approached Venerable Sāriputta, and exchanged greetings with him. "

msgctxt "mn97:2.3"
msgid "Sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinnaṃ kho taṃ bhikkhuṃ āyasmā sāriputto etadavoca: "
msgstr "When the greetings and polite conversation were over, he sat down to one side. Sāriputta said to him, "

msgctxt "mn97:2.4"
msgid "“kaccāvuso, bhagavā arogo ca balavā cā”ti? "
msgstr "“Reverend, I hope the Buddha is healthy and well?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn97:2.5"
msgid "“Arogo cāvuso, bhagavā balavā cā”ti. "
msgstr "“He is, reverend.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn97:2.6"
msgid "“Kacci panāvuso, bhikkhusaṃgho arogo ca balavā cā”ti? "
msgstr "“And I hope that the mendicant Saṅgha is healthy and well.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn97:2.7"
msgid "“Bhikkhusaṃghopi kho, āvuso, arogo ca balavā cā”ti. "
msgstr "“It is.” "

# NOTE: BB has “living at the Taṇḍulapāla Gate”, DPPN has “Near the gate was the residence of the brahmin Dhānañjāni.” But it is notable that none of the usual terms for staying or residence are found here (viharati, nivesati, etc.). Nor is this place mentioned elsewhere as his residence. Now, tandula means “rice”, “pala/pali “means” guard”, and dvara is a gate or door. I think Dhananjani was an official who worked at the gate, which was a checkpoint for the movement of rice in and out of the city. It was, i suspect, in this capacity that he was able to to skim off funds.
#. HTML: </p><p>
#. VAR: dhanañjāni → dhānañjāni (pts1)
msgctxt "mn97:2.8"
msgid "“Ettha, āvuso, taṇḍulapālidvārāya dhanañjāni nāma brāhmaṇo atthi. "
msgstr "“Reverend, at the rice checkpoint there is a brahmin named Dhanañjāni. "

msgctxt "mn97:2.9"
msgid "Kaccāvuso, dhanañjāni brāhmaṇo arogo ca balavā cā”ti? "
msgstr "I hope that he is healthy and well?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn97:2.10"
msgid "“Dhanañjānipi kho, āvuso, brāhmaṇo arogo ca balavā cā”ti. "
msgstr "“He too is well.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn97:2.11"
msgid "“Kacci panāvuso, dhanañjāni brāhmaṇo appamatto”ti? "
msgstr "“But is he diligent?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn97:2.12"
msgid "“Kuto panāvuso, dhanañjānissa brāhmaṇassa appamādo? "
msgstr "“How could he possibly be diligent? "

msgctxt "mn97:2.13"
msgid "Dhanañjāni, āvuso, brāhmaṇo rājānaṃ nissāya brāhmaṇagahapatike vilumpati, brāhmaṇagahapatike nissāya rājānaṃ vilumpati. "
msgstr "Dhanañjāni robs the brahmins and householders in the name of the king, and he robs the king in the name of the brahmins and householders. "

msgctxt "mn97:2.14"
msgid "Yāpissa bhariyā saddhā saddhakulā ānītā sāpi kālaṅkatā; "
msgstr "His wife, a lady of faith who he married from a family of faith, has passed away. "

msgctxt "mn97:2.15"
msgid "aññāssa bhariyā assaddhā assaddhakulā ānītā”ti. "
msgstr "And he has taken a new wife who has no faith.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn97:2.16"
msgid "“Dussutaṃ vatāvuso, assumha, dussutaṃ vatāvuso, assumha; "
msgstr "“Oh, it’s bad news "

msgctxt "mn97:2.17"
msgid "ye mayaṃ dhanañjāniṃ brāhmaṇaṃ pamattaṃ assumha. "
msgstr "to hear that Dhanañjāni is negligent. "

msgctxt "mn97:2.18"
msgid "Appeva ca nāma mayaṃ kadāci karahaci dhanañjāninā brāhmaṇena saddhiṃ samāgaccheyyāma, appeva nāma siyā kocideva kathāsallāpo”ti? "
msgstr "Hopefully, some time or other I’ll get to meet him, and we can have a discussion.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya3, pts-vp-pli2.186, sc2
msgctxt "mn97:3.1"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā sāriputto dakkhiṇāgirismiṃ yathābhirantaṃ viharitvā yena rājagahaṃ tena cārikaṃ pakkāmi. "
msgstr "When Sāriputta had stayed in the Southern Hills as long as he wished, he set out for Rājagaha. "

msgctxt "mn97:3.2"
msgid "Anupubbena cārikaṃ caramāno yena rājagahaṃ tadavasari. "
msgstr "Traveling stage by stage, he arrived at Rājagaha, "

msgctxt "mn97:3.3"
msgid "Tatra sudaṃ āyasmā sāriputto rājagahe viharati veḷuvane kalandakanivāpe. "
msgstr "where he stayed in the Bamboo Grove, the squirrels’ feeding ground. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya4
msgctxt "mn97:4.1"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā sāriputto pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya rājagahaṃ piṇḍāya pāvisi. "
msgstr "Then he robed up in the morning and, taking his bowl and robe, entered Rājagaha for alms. "

msgctxt "mn97:4.2"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena dhanañjāni brāhmaṇo bahinagare gāvo goṭṭhe duhāpeti. "
msgstr "Now at that time Dhanañjāni was having his cows milked in a cow-shed outside the city. "

msgctxt "mn97:4.3"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā sāriputto rājagahe piṇḍāya caritvā pacchābhattaṃ piṇḍapātapaṭikkanto yena dhanañjāni brāhmaṇo tenupasaṅkami. "
msgstr "Then Sāriputta wandered for alms in Rājagaha. After the meal, on his return from alms-round, he approached Dhanañjāni. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn97:4.4"
msgid "Addasā kho dhanañjāni brāhmaṇo āyasmantaṃ sāriputtaṃ dūratova āgacchantaṃ. "
msgstr "Seeing Sāriputta coming off in the distance, "

msgctxt "mn97:4.5"
msgid "Disvāna yenāyasmā sāriputto tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā āyasmantaṃ sāriputtaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "Dhanañjāni went to him and said, "

msgctxt "mn97:4.6"
msgid "“ito, bho sāriputta, payo, pīyataṃ tāva bhattassa kālo bhavissatī”ti. "
msgstr "“Here, Master Sāriputta, drink some fresh milk before the meal time.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn97:4.7"
msgid "“Alaṃ, brāhmaṇa. "
msgstr "“Enough, brahmin, "

msgctxt "mn97:4.8"
msgid "Kataṃ me ajja bhattakiccaṃ. "
msgstr "I’ve finished eating for today. "

msgctxt "mn97:4.9"
msgid "Amukasmiṃ me rukkhamūle divāvihāro bhavissati. "
msgstr "I shall be at the root of that tree for the day’s meditation. "

msgctxt "mn97:4.10"
msgid "Tattha āgaccheyyāsī”ti. "
msgstr "Come see me there.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn97:4.11"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bho”ti kho dhanañjāni brāhmaṇo āyasmato sāriputtassa paccassosi. "
msgstr "“Yes, sir,” replied Dhanañjāni. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya5
msgctxt "mn97:5.1"
msgid "Atha kho dhanañjāni brāhmaṇo pacchābhattaṃ bhuttapātarāso yenāyasmā sāriputto tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā āyasmatā sāriputtena saddhiṃ sammodi. "
msgstr "When Dhanañjāni had finished breakfast he went to Sāriputta and exchanged greetings with him. "

msgctxt "mn97:5.2"
msgid "Sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinnaṃ kho dhanañjāniṃ brāhmaṇaṃ āyasmā sāriputto etadavoca: "
msgstr "When the greetings and polite conversation were over, he sat down to one side. Sāriputta said to him, "

msgctxt "mn97:5.3"
msgid "“kaccāsi, dhanañjāni, appamatto”ti? "
msgstr "“I hope you’re diligent, Dhanañjāni?” "

# NOTE: As for karaniya katabba, this is clearly referring to the bali as at AN 4.61, AN 5.41. For the last two verbs, BB has “refreshed and nourished”. But pinetabbo is probably from pīṇa = fat, swollen, agreeing with bruheti, to increase. These terms are probably unique in this context, and contrast with the expected poseti found earlier. It speaks, I think, to Dhananjani’s sense of entitlement: he merely has to provide for his family, but he must fatten himself.
#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn97:5.4"
msgid "“Kuto, bho sāriputta, amhākaṃ appamādo yesaṃ no mātāpitaro posetabbā, puttadāro posetabbo, dāsakammakarā posetabbā, mittāmaccānaṃ mittāmaccakaraṇīyaṃ kātabbaṃ, ñātisālohitānaṃ ñātisālohitakaraṇīyaṃ kātabbaṃ, atithīnaṃ atithikaraṇīyaṃ kātabbaṃ, pubbapetānaṃ pubbapetakaraṇīyaṃ kātabbaṃ, devatānaṃ devatākaraṇīyaṃ kātabbaṃ, rañño rājakaraṇīyaṃ kātabbaṃ, ayampi kāyo pīṇetabbo brūhetabbo”ti? "
msgstr "“How can I possibly be diligent, Master Sāriputta? I have to provide for my mother and father, my wives and children, and my bondservants and workers. And I have to make the proper offerings to friends and colleagues, relatives and kin, guests, ancestors, deities, and king. And then this body must also be fattened and built up.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya6, pts-vp-pli2.187, sc3
msgctxt "mn97:6.1"
msgid "“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, dhanañjāni, "
msgstr "“What do you think, Dhanañjāni? "

msgctxt "mn97:6.2"
msgid "idhekacco mātāpitūnaṃ hetu adhammacārī visamacārī assa, tamenaṃ adhammacariyāvisamacariyāhetu nirayaṃ nirayapālā upakaḍḍheyyuṃ. "
msgstr "Suppose someone was to behave in an unprincipled and unjust way for the sake of their parents. Because of this the wardens of hell would drag them to hell. "

msgctxt "mn97:6.3"
msgid "Labheyya nu kho so ‘ahaṃ kho mātāpitūnaṃ hetu adhammacārī visamacārī ahosiṃ, mā maṃ nirayaṃ nirayapālā’ti, mātāpitaro vā panassa labheyyuṃ ‘eso kho amhākaṃ hetu adhammacārī visamacārī ahosi, mā naṃ nirayaṃ nirayapālā’”ti? "
msgstr "Could they get out of being dragged to hell by pleading that they had acted for the sake of their parents? Or could their parents save them by pleading that the acts had been done for their sake?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn97:6.4"
msgid "“No hidaṃ, bho sāriputta. "
msgstr "“No, Master Sāriputta. "

msgctxt "mn97:6.5"
msgid "Atha kho naṃ vikkandantaṃyeva niraye nirayapālā pakkhipeyyuṃ”. "
msgstr "Rather, even as they were wailing the wardens of hell would cast them down into hell.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya7, sc4
msgctxt "mn97:7.1"
msgid "“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, dhanañjāni, "
msgstr "“What do you think, Dhanañjāni? "

msgctxt "mn97:7.2"
msgid "idhekacco puttadārassa hetu adhammacārī visamacārī assa, tamenaṃ adhammacariyāvisamacariyāhetu nirayaṃ nirayapālā upakaḍḍheyyuṃ. "
msgstr "Suppose someone was to behave in an unprincipled and unjust way for the sake of their wives and children … "

msgctxt "mn97:7.3"
msgid "Labheyya nu kho so ‘ahaṃ kho puttadārassa hetu adhammacārī visamacārī ahosiṃ, mā maṃ nirayaṃ nirayapālā’ti, puttadāro vā panassa labheyya ‘eso kho amhākaṃ hetu adhammacārī visamacārī ahosi mā naṃ nirayaṃ nirayapālā’”ti? "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn97:7.4"
msgid "“No hidaṃ, bho sāriputta. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn97:7.5"
msgid "Atha kho naṃ vikkandantaṃyeva niraye nirayapālā pakkhipeyyuṃ”. "
msgstr " "

#. REF: nya8, sc5
msgctxt "mn97:8.1"
msgid "“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, dhanañjāni, idhekacco dāsakammakaraporisassa hetu adhammacārī visamacārī assa, tamenaṃ adhammacariyāvisamacariyāhetu nirayaṃ nirayapālā upakaḍḍheyyuṃ. "
msgstr "bondservants and workers … "

msgctxt "mn97:8.2"
msgid "Labheyya nu kho so ‘ahaṃ kho dāsakammakaraporisassa hetu adhammacārī visamacārī ahosiṃ, mā maṃ nirayaṃ nirayapālā’ti, dāsakammakaraporisā vā panassa labheyyuṃ ‘eso kho amhākaṃ hetu adhammacārī visamacārī ahosi, mā naṃ nirayaṃ nirayapālā’”ti? "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn97:8.3"
msgid "“No hidaṃ, bho sāriputta. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn97:8.4"
msgid "Atha kho naṃ vikkandantaṃyeva niraye nirayapālā pakkhipeyyuṃ”. "
msgstr " "

#. REF: nya9, sc6
msgctxt "mn97:9.1"
msgid "“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, dhanañjāni, idhekacco mittāmaccānaṃ hetu adhammacārī visamacārī assa, tamenaṃ adhammacariyāvisamacariyāhetu nirayaṃ nirayapālā upakaḍḍheyyuṃ. "
msgstr "friends and colleagues … "

msgctxt "mn97:9.2"
msgid "Labheyya nu kho so ‘ahaṃ kho mittāmaccānaṃ hetu adhammacārī visamacārī ahosiṃ, mā maṃ nirayaṃ nirayapālā’ti, mittāmaccā vā panassa labheyyuṃ ‘eso kho amhākaṃ hetu adhammacārī visamacārī ahosi, mā naṃ nirayaṃ nirayapālā’”ti? "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn97:9.3"
msgid "“No hidaṃ, bho sāriputta. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn97:9.4"
msgid "Atha kho naṃ vikkandantaṃyeva niraye nirayapālā pakkhipeyyuṃ”. "
msgstr " "

#. REF: nya10, sc7
msgctxt "mn97:10.1"
msgid "“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, dhanañjāni, idhekacco ñātisālohitānaṃ hetu adhammacārī visamacārī assa, tamenaṃ adhammacariyāvisamacariyāhetu nirayaṃ nirayapālā upakaḍḍheyyuṃ. "
msgstr "relatives and kin … "

msgctxt "mn97:10.2"
msgid "Labheyya nu kho so ‘ahaṃ kho ñātisālohitānaṃ hetu adhammacārī visamacārī ahosiṃ, mā maṃ nirayaṃ nirayapālā’ti, ñātisālohitā vā panassa labheyyuṃ ‘eso kho amhākaṃ hetu adhammacārī visamacārī ahosi, mā naṃ nirayaṃ nirayapālā’”ti? "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn97:10.3"
msgid "“No hidaṃ, bho sāriputta. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn97:10.4"
msgid "Atha kho naṃ vikkandantaṃyeva niraye nirayapālā pakkhipeyyuṃ”. "
msgstr " "

