msgstr " "

#. REF: nya14, sc11
msgctxt "mn97:14.1"
msgid "“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, dhanañjāni, idhekacco rañño hetu adhammacārī visamacārī assa, tamenaṃ adhammacariyāvisamacariyāhetu nirayaṃ nirayapālā upakaḍḍheyyuṃ. "
msgstr "king … "

msgctxt "mn97:14.2"
msgid "Labheyya nu kho so ‘ahaṃ kho rañño hetu adhammacārī visamacārī ahosiṃ, mā maṃ nirayaṃ nirayapālā’ti, rājā vā panassa labheyya ‘eso kho amhākaṃ hetu adhammacārī visamacārī ahosi, mā naṃ nirayaṃ nirayapālā’”ti? "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn97:14.3"
msgid "“No hidaṃ, bho sāriputta. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn97:14.4"
msgid "Atha kho naṃ vikkandantaṃyeva niraye nirayapālā pakkhipeyyuṃ”. "
msgstr " "

#. REF: nya15, sc12
msgctxt "mn97:15.1"
msgid "“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, dhanañjāni, idhekacco kāyassa pīṇanāhetu brūhanāhetu adhammacārī visamacārī assa, tamenaṃ adhammacariyāvisamacariyāhetu nirayaṃ nirayapālā upakaḍḍheyyuṃ. "
msgstr "fattening and building up their body. Because of this the wardens of hell would drag them to hell. "

msgctxt "mn97:15.2"
msgid "Labheyya nu kho so ‘ahaṃ kho kāyassa pīṇanāhetu brūhanāhetu adhammacārī visamacārī ahosiṃ, mā maṃ nirayaṃ nirayapālā’ti, pare vā panassa labheyyuṃ ‘eso kho kāyassa pīṇanāhetu brūhanāhetu adhammacārī visamacārī ahosi, mā naṃ nirayaṃ nirayapālā’”ti? "
msgstr "Could they get out of being dragged to hell by pleading that they had acted for the sake of fattening and building up their body? Or could anyone else save them by pleading that the acts had been done for that reason?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn97:15.3"
msgid "“No hidaṃ, bho sāriputta. "
msgstr "“No, Master Sāriputta. "

msgctxt "mn97:15.4"
msgid "Atha kho naṃ vikkandantaṃyeva niraye nirayapālā pakkhipeyyuṃ”. "
msgstr "Rather, even as they were wailing the wardens of hell would cast them down into hell.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya16, sc13
msgctxt "mn97:16.1"
msgid "“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, dhanañjāni, yo vā mātāpitūnaṃ hetu adhammacārī visamacārī assa, yo vā mātāpitūnaṃ hetu dhammacārī samacārī assa; "
msgstr "“Who do you think is better, Dhanañjāni? Someone who, for the sake of their parents, behaves in an unprincipled and unjust manner, or someone who behaves in a principled and just manner?” "

msgctxt "mn97:16.2"
msgid "katamaṃ seyyo”ti? "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn97:16.3"
msgid "“Yo hi, bho sāriputta, mātāpitūnaṃ hetu adhammacārī visamacārī assa, na taṃ seyyo; "
msgstr "“Someone who behaves in a principled and just manner for the sake of their parents. "

msgctxt "mn97:16.4"
msgid "yo ca kho, bho sāriputta, mātāpitūnaṃ hetu dhammacārī samacārī assa, tadevettha seyyo. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn97:16.5"
msgid "Adhammacariyāvisamacariyāhi, bho sāriputta, dhammacariyāsamacariyā seyyo”ti. "
msgstr "For principled and moral conduct is better than unprincipled and immoral conduct.” "

# NOTE: Reading anne for annesam as in PTS edition. otherwise it would be “others have livelihoods …”
#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn97:16.6"
msgid "“Atthi kho, dhanañjāni, aññesaṃ hetukā dhammikā kammantā, yehi sakkā mātāpitaro ceva posetuṃ, na ca pāpakammaṃ kātuṃ, puññañca paṭipadaṃ paṭipajjituṃ. "
msgstr "“Dhanañjāni, there are other livelihoods that are both profitable and legitimate. By means of these it’s possible to provide for your parents, avoid bad deeds, and practice the path of goodness. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya17, pts-vp-pli2.189, sc14
