msgstr "For principled and moral conduct is better than unprincipled and immoral conduct.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn97:25.6"
msgid "“Atthi kho, dhanañjāni, aññesaṃ hetukā dhammikā kammantā, yehi sakkā kāyañceva pīṇetuṃ brūhetuṃ, na ca pāpakammaṃ kātuṃ, puññañca paṭipadaṃ paṭipajjitun”ti. "
msgstr "“Dhanañjāni, there are other livelihoods that are both profitable and legitimate. By means of these it’s possible to fatten and build up your body, avoid bad deeds, and practice the path of goodness.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya26, pts-vp-pli2.192, sc23
msgctxt "mn97:26.1"
msgid "Atha kho dhanañjāni brāhmaṇo āyasmato sāriputtassa bhāsitaṃ abhinanditvā anumoditvā uṭṭhāyāsanā pakkāmi. "
msgstr "Then Dhanañjāni the brahmin, having approved and agreed with what Venerable Sāriputta said, got up from his seat and left. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya27
msgctxt "mn97:27.1"
msgid "Atha kho dhanañjāni brāhmaṇo aparena samayena ābādhiko ahosi dukkhito bāḷhagilāno. "
msgstr "Some time later Dhanañjāni became sick, suffering, gravely ill. "

msgctxt "mn97:27.2"
msgid "Atha kho dhanañjāni brāhmaṇo aññataraṃ purisaṃ āmantesi: "
msgstr "Then he addressed a man, "

msgctxt "mn97:27.3"
msgid "“ehi tvaṃ, ambho purisa, yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkama; upasaṅkamitvā mama vacanena bhagavato pāde sirasā vandāhi: "
msgstr "“Please, mister, go to the Buddha, and in my name bow with your head to his feet. Say to him: "

msgctxt "mn97:27.4"
msgid "‘dhanañjāni, bhante, brāhmaṇo ābādhiko dukkhito bāḷhagilāno. "
msgstr "‘Sir, the brahmin Dhanañjāni is sick, suffering, gravely ill. "

msgctxt "mn97:27.5"
msgid "So bhagavato pāde sirasā vandatī’ti. "
msgstr "He bows with his head to your feet.’ "

msgctxt "mn97:27.6"
msgid "Yena cāyasmā sāriputto tenupasaṅkama; upasaṅkamitvā mama vacanena āyasmato sāriputtassa pāde sirasā vandāhi: "
msgstr "Then go to Venerable Sāriputta, and in my name bow with your head to his feet. Say to him: "

msgctxt "mn97:27.7"
msgid "‘dhanañjāni, bhante, brāhmaṇo ābādhiko dukkhito bāḷhagilāno. "
msgstr "‘Sir, the brahmin Dhanañjāni is sick, suffering, gravely ill. "

msgctxt "mn97:27.8"
msgid "So āyasmato sāriputtassa pāde sirasā vandatī’ti. "
msgstr "He bows with his head to your feet.’ "

msgctxt "mn97:27.9"
msgid "Evañca vadehi: "
msgstr "And then say: "

msgctxt "mn97:27.10"
msgid "‘sādhu kira, bhante, āyasmā sāriputto yena dhanañjānissa brāhmaṇassa nivesanaṃ tenupasaṅkamatu anukampaṃ upādāyā’”ti. "
msgstr "‘Sir, please visit Dhanañjāni at his home out of compassion.’” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn97:27.11"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho so puriso dhanañjānissa brāhmaṇassa paṭissutvā yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho so puriso bhagavantaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "“Yes, sir,” that man replied. He did as Dhanañjāni asked. "

msgctxt "mn97:27.12"
msgid "“dhanañjāni, bhante, brāhmaṇo ābādhiko dukkhito bāḷhagilāno. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn97:27.13"
msgid "So bhagavato pāde sirasā vandatī”ti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn97:27.14"
msgid "Yena cāyasmā sāriputto tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā āyasmantaṃ sāriputtaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho so puriso āyasmantaṃ sāriputtaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn97:27.15"
msgid "“dhanañjāni, bhante, brāhmaṇo ābādhiko dukkhito bāḷhagilāno. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn97:27.16"
msgid "So āyasmato sāriputtassa pāde sirasā vandati, evañca vadeti: "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn97:27.17"
msgid "‘sādhu kira, bhante, āyasmā sāriputto yena dhanañjānissa brāhmaṇassa nivesanaṃ tenupasaṅkamatu anukampaṃ upādāyā’”ti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn97:27.18"
msgid "Adhivāsesi kho āyasmā sāriputto tuṇhībhāvena. "
msgstr "Sāriputta consented in silence. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya28, pts-vp-pli2.193, sc24
msgctxt "mn97:28.1"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā sāriputto nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya yena dhanañjānissa brāhmaṇassa nivesanaṃ tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā paññatte āsane nisīdi. Nisajja kho āyasmā sāriputto dhanañjāniṃ brāhmaṇaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "He robed up, and, taking his bowl and robe, went to Dhanañjāni’s home, where he sat on the seat spread out and said to Dhanañjāni, "

msgctxt "mn97:28.2"
msgid "“kacci te, dhanañjāni, khamanīyaṃ, kacci yāpanīyaṃ? Kacci dukkhā vedanā paṭikkamanti, no abhikkamanti? Paṭikkamosānaṃ paññāyati, no abhikkamo”ti? "
msgstr "“Dhanañjāni, I hope you’re keeping well; I hope you’re alright. And I hope the pain is fading, not growing, that its fading is evident, not its growing.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya29
msgctxt "mn97:29.1"
msgid "“Na me, bho sāriputta, khamanīyaṃ na yāpanīyaṃ. Bāḷhā me dukkhā vedanā abhikkamanti, no paṭikkamanti. Abhikkamosānaṃ paññāyati, no paṭikkamo. "
msgstr "“I’m not keeping well, Master Sāriputta, I’m not alright. The pain is terrible and growing, not fading; its growing is evident, not its fading. "

#. VAR: muddhani → muddhānaṃ (s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "mn97:29.2"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, bho sāriputta, balavā puriso tiṇhena sikharena muddhani abhimattheyya; evameva kho, bho sāriputta, adhimattā vātā muddhani ca ūhananti. "
msgstr "The winds piercing my head are so severe, it feels like a strong man drilling into my head with a sharp point. "

msgctxt "mn97:29.3"
msgid "Na me, bho sāriputta, khamanīyaṃ, na yāpanīyaṃ. Bāḷhā me dukkhā vedanā abhikkamanti, no paṭikkamanti. Abhikkamosānaṃ paññāyati, no paṭikkamo. "
msgstr "I’m not keeping well. "

msgctxt "mn97:29.4"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, bho sāriputta, balavā puriso daḷhena varattakkhaṇḍena sīse sīsaveṭhaṃ dadeyya; evameva kho, bho sāriputta, adhimattā sīse sīsavedanā. "
msgstr "The pain in my head is so severe, it feels like a strong man tightening a tough leather strap around my head. "

msgctxt "mn97:29.5"
msgid "Na me, bho sāriputta, khamanīyaṃ na yāpanīyaṃ. Bāḷhā me dukkhā vedanā abhikkamanti, no paṭikkamanti. Abhikkamosānaṃ paññāyati, no paṭikkamo. "
msgstr "I’m not keeping well. "

msgctxt "mn97:29.6"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, bho sāriputta, dakkho goghātako vā goghātakantevāsī vā tiṇhena govikantanena kucchiṃ parikanteyya; evameva kho, bho sāriputta, adhimattā vātā kucchiṃ parikantanti. "
msgstr "The winds piercing my belly are so severe, it feels like a deft butcher or their apprentice is slicing my belly open with a meat cleaver. "

msgctxt "mn97:29.7"
msgid "Na me, bho sāriputta, khamanīyaṃ, na yāpanīyaṃ. Bāḷhā me dukkhā vedanā abhikkamanti, no paṭikkamanti. Abhikkamosānaṃ paññāyati, no paṭikkamo. "
msgstr "I’m not keeping well. "

msgctxt "mn97:29.8"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, bho sāriputta, dve balavanto purisā dubbalataraṃ purisaṃ nānābāhāsu gahetvā aṅgārakāsuyā santāpeyyuṃ samparitāpeyyuṃ; evameva kho, bho sāriputta, adhimatto kāyasmiṃ ḍāho. "
msgstr "The burning in my body is so severe, it feels like two strong men grabbing a weaker man by the arms to burn and scorch him on a pit of glowing coals. "

msgctxt "mn97:29.9"
msgid "Na me, bho sāriputta, khamanīyaṃ na yāpanīyaṃ. Bāḷhā me dukkhā vedanā abhikkamanti, no paṭikkamanti. Abhikkamosānaṃ paññāyati, no paṭikkamo”ti. "
msgstr "I’m not keeping well, Master Sāriputta, I’m not alright. The pain is terrible and growing, not fading; its growing is evident, not its fading.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya30, pts-vp-pli2.194, sc25
msgctxt "mn97:30.1"
msgid "“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, dhanañjāni, katamaṃ seyyo—"
msgstr "“Dhanañjāni, which do you think is better: "

msgctxt "mn97:30.2"
msgid "nirayo vā tiracchānayoni vā”ti? "
msgstr "hell or the animal realm?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn97:30.3"
msgid "“Nirayā, bho sāriputta, tiracchānayoni seyyo”ti. "
msgstr "“The animal realm is better.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn97:30.4"
msgid "“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, dhanañjāni, katamaṃ seyyo—"
msgstr "“Which do you think is better: "

msgctxt "mn97:30.5"
msgid "tiracchānayoni vā pettivisayo vā”ti? "
msgstr "the animal realm or the ghost realm?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn97:30.6"
msgid "“Tiracchānayoniyā, bho sāriputta, pettivisayo seyyo”ti. "
msgstr "“The ghost realm is better.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn97:30.7"
msgid "“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, dhanañjāni, katamaṃ seyyo—"
msgstr "“Which do you think is better: "

msgctxt "mn97:30.8"
msgid "pettivisayo vā manussā vā”ti? "
msgstr "the ghost realm or human life?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn97:30.9"
msgid "“Pettivisayā, bho sāriputta, manussā seyyo”ti. "
msgstr "“Human life is better.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn97:30.10"
msgid "“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, dhanañjāni, katamaṃ seyyo—"
msgstr "“Which do you think is better: "

#. VAR: cātumahārājikā → cātum­mahārā­jikā (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "mn97:30.11"
msgid "manussā vā cātumahārājikā vā devā”ti? "
msgstr "human life or as one of the Gods of the Four Great Kings?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn97:30.12"
msgid "“Manussehi, bho sāriputta, cātumahārājikā devā seyyo”ti. "
msgstr "“The Gods of the Four Great Kings.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn97:30.13"
msgid "“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, dhanañjāni, katamaṃ seyyo—"
msgstr "“Which do you think is better: "

msgctxt "mn97:30.14"
msgid "cātumahārājikā vā devā tāvatiṃsā vā devā”ti? "
msgstr "the Gods of the Four Great Kings or the Gods of the Thirty-Three?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn97:30.15"
msgid "“Cātumahārājikehi, bho sāriputta, devehi tāvatiṃsā devā seyyo”ti. "
msgstr "“The Gods of the Thirty-Three.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn97:30.16"
msgid "“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, dhanañjāni, katamaṃ seyyo—"
msgstr "“Which do you think is better: "

msgctxt "mn97:30.17"
msgid "tāvatiṃsā vā devā yāmā vā devā”ti? "
msgstr "the Gods of the Thirty-Three or the Gods of Yama?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn97:30.18"
msgid "“Tāvatiṃsehi, bho sāriputta, devehi yāmā devā seyyo”ti. "
msgstr "“The Gods of Yama.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn97:30.19"
msgid "“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, dhanañjāni, katamaṃ seyyo—"
msgstr "“Which do you think is better: "

msgctxt "mn97:30.20"
msgid "yāmā vā devā tusitā vā devā”ti? "
msgstr "the Gods of Yama or the Joyful Gods?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn97:30.21"
msgid "“Yāmehi, bho sāriputta, devehi tusitā devā seyyo”ti. "
msgstr "“The Joyful Gods.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn97:30.22"
msgid "“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, dhanañjāni, katamaṃ seyyo—"
msgstr "“Which do you think is better: "

msgctxt "mn97:30.23"
msgid "tusitā vā devā nimmānaratī vā devā”ti? "
msgstr "the Joyful Gods or the Gods Who Love to Create?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn97:30.24"
msgid "“Tusitehi, bho sāriputta, devehi nimmānaratī devā seyyo”ti. "
msgstr "“The Gods Who Love to Create.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn97:30.25"
msgid "“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, dhanañjāni, katamaṃ seyyo—"
msgstr "“Which do you think is better: "

msgctxt "mn97:30.26"
msgid "nimmānaratī vā devā paranimmitavasavattī vā devā”ti? "
msgstr "the Gods Who Love to Create or the Gods Who Control the Creations of Others?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn97:30.27"
msgid "“Nimmānaratīhi, bho sāriputta, devehi paranimmitavasavattī devā seyyo”ti. "
msgstr "“The Gods Who Control the Creations of Others.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya31
msgctxt "mn97:31.1"
msgid "“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, dhanañjāni, katamaṃ seyyo "
msgstr "“Which do you think is better: "

msgctxt "mn97:31.2"
msgid "paranimmitavasavattī vā devā brahmaloko vā”ti? "
msgstr "the Gods Who Control the Creations of Others or the Brahmā realm?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn97:31.3"
msgid "“‘Brahmaloko’ti—bhavaṃ sāriputto āha; "
msgstr "“Master Sāriputta speaks of the Brahmā realm! "

msgctxt "mn97:31.4"
msgid "‘brahmaloko’ti—bhavaṃ sāriputto āhā”ti. "
msgstr "Master Sāriputta speaks of the Brahmā realm!” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli2.195, sc26
msgctxt "mn97:31.5"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmato sāriputtassa etadahosi: "
msgstr "Then Sāriputta thought: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn97:31.6"
msgid "“ime kho brāhmaṇā brahmalokādhimuttā. "
msgstr "“These brahmins are devoted to the Brahmā realm. "

msgctxt "mn97:31.7"
msgid "Yannūnāhaṃ dhanañjānissa brāhmaṇassa brahmānaṃ sahabyatāya maggaṃ deseyyan”ti. "
msgstr "Why don’t I teach him a path to the company of Brahmā?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn97:31.8"
msgid "“Brahmānaṃ te, dhanañjāni, sahabyatāya maggaṃ desessāmi; "
msgstr "“Dhanañjāni, I shall teach you a path to the company of Brahmā. "

msgctxt "mn97:31.9"
msgid "taṃ suṇāhi, sādhukaṃ manasi karohi, bhāsissāmī”ti. "
msgstr "Listen and pay close attention, I will speak.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn97:31.10"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bho”ti kho dhanañjāni brāhmaṇo āyasmato sāriputtassa paccassosi. "
msgstr "“Yes, sir,” replied Dhanañjāni. "

msgctxt "mn97:31.11"
msgid "Āyasmā sāriputto etadavoca: "
msgstr "Venerable Sāriputta said this: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya32
msgctxt "mn97:32.1"
msgid "“katamo ca, dhanañjāni, brahmānaṃ sahabyatāya maggo? "
msgstr "“And what is a path to companionship with Brahmā? "

msgctxt "mn97:32.2"
msgid "Idha, dhanañjāni, bhikkhu mettāsahagatena cetasā ekaṃ disaṃ pharitvā viharati, tathā dutiyaṃ, tathā tatiyaṃ, tathā catutthaṃ; iti uddhamadho tiriyaṃ sabbadhi sabbattatāya sabbāvantaṃ lokaṃ mettāsahagatena cetasā vipulena mahaggatena appamāṇena averena abyābajjhena pharitvā viharati. "
msgstr "Firstly, a mendicant meditates spreading a heart full of love to one direction, and to the second, and to the third, and to the fourth. In the same way above, below, across, everywhere, all around, they spread a heart full of love to the whole world—abundant, expansive, limitless, free of enmity and ill will. "

msgctxt "mn97:32.3"
msgid "Ayaṃ kho, dhanañjāni, brahmānaṃ sahabyatāya maggo. "
msgstr "This is a path to companionship with Brahmā. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya33-35, sc27
msgctxt "mn97:33-35.1"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, dhanañjāni, bhikkhu karuṇāsahagatena cetasā … pe … "
msgstr "Furthermore, a mendicant meditates spreading a heart full of compassion … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn97:33-35.2"
msgid "muditāsahagatena cetasā … "
msgstr "They meditate spreading a heart full of rejoicing … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn97:33-35.3"
msgid "upekkhāsahagatena cetasā ekaṃ disaṃ pharitvā viharati, tathā dutiyaṃ, tathā tatiyaṃ, tathā catutthaṃ; iti uddhamadho tiriyaṃ sabbadhi sabbattatāya sabbāvantaṃ lokaṃ upekkhāsahagatena cetasā vipulena mahaggatena appamāṇena averena abyābajjhena pharitvā viharati. "
msgstr "They meditate spreading a heart full of equanimity to one direction, and to the second, and to the third, and to the fourth. In the same way above, below, across, everywhere, all around, they spread a heart full of equanimity to the whole world—abundant, expansive, limitless, free of enmity and ill will. "

msgctxt "mn97:33-35.4"
msgid "Ayaṃ kho, dhanañjāni, brahmānaṃ sahabyatāya maggo”ti. "
msgstr "This is a path to companionship with Brahmā.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya36
msgctxt "mn97:36.1"
msgid "“Tena hi, bho sāriputta, mama vacanena bhagavato pāde sirasā vandāhi: "
msgstr "“Well then, Master Sāriputta, in my name bow with your head to the Buddha’s feet. Say to him: "

msgctxt "mn97:36.2"
msgid "‘dhanañjāni, bhante, brāhmaṇo ābādhiko dukkhito bāḷhagilāno. "
msgstr "‘Sir, the brahmin Dhanañjāni is sick, suffering, gravely ill. "

msgctxt "mn97:36.3"
msgid "So bhagavato pāde sirasā vandatī’”ti. "
msgstr "He bows with his head to your feet.’” "

msgctxt "mn97:36.4"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā sāriputto dhanañjāniṃ brāhmaṇaṃ sati uttarikaraṇīye hīne brahmaloke patiṭṭhāpetvā uṭṭhāyāsanā pakkāmi. "
msgstr "Then Sāriputta, after establishing Dhanañjāni in the inferior Brahmā realm, got up from his seat and left while there was still more left to do. "

msgctxt "mn97:36.5"
msgid "Atha kho dhanañjāni brāhmaṇo acirapakkante āyasmante sāriputte kālamakāsi, brahmalokañca upapajji. "
msgstr "Not long after Sāriputta had departed, Dhanañjāni passed away and was reborn in the Brahmā realm. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya37, pts-vp-pli2.196, sc28
msgctxt "mn97:37.1"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi: "
msgstr "Then the Buddha said to the mendicants, "

msgctxt "mn97:37.2"
msgid "“eso, bhikkhave, sāriputto dhanañjāniṃ brāhmaṇaṃ sati uttarikaraṇīye hīne brahmaloke patiṭṭhāpetvā uṭṭhāyāsanā pakkanto”ti. "
msgstr "“Mendicants, Sāriputta, after establishing Dhanañjāni in the inferior Brahmā realm, got up from his seat and left while there was still more left to do.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya38
msgctxt "mn97:38.1"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā sāriputto yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami, upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi, ekamantaṃ nisinno kho āyasmā sāriputto bhagavantaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "Then Sāriputta went to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side, and said, "

msgctxt "mn97:38.2"
msgid "“dhanañjāni, bhante, brāhmaṇo ābādhiko dukkhito bāḷhagilāno, "
msgstr "“Sir, the brahmin Dhanañjāni is sick, suffering, gravely ill. "

msgctxt "mn97:38.3"
msgid "so bhagavato pāde sirasā vandatī”ti. "
msgstr "He bows with his head to your feet.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn97:38.4"
msgid "“Kiṃ pana tvaṃ, sāriputta, dhanañjāniṃ brāhmaṇaṃ sati uttarikaraṇīye hīne brahmaloke patiṭṭhāpetvā uṭṭhāyāsanā pakkanto”ti? "
msgstr "“But Sāriputta, after establishing Dhanañjāni in the inferior Brahmā realm, why did you get up from your seat and leave while there was still more left to do?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn97:38.5"
msgid "“Mayhaṃ kho, bhante, evaṃ ahosi: "
msgstr "“Sir, I thought: "

msgctxt "mn97:38.6"
msgid "‘ime kho brāhmaṇā brahmalokādhimuttā, yannūnāhaṃ dhanañjānissa brāhmaṇassa brahmānaṃ sahabyatāya maggaṃ deseyyan’”ti. "
msgstr "‘These brahmins are devoted to the Brahmā realm. Why don’t I teach him a path to the company of Brahmā?’” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. VAR: Kālaṅkato ca → kālakato ca (bj, pts1) | kālakatova (s1-3) | kālaṅkatova (km, mr)
msgctxt "mn97:38.7"
msgid "“Kālaṅkato ca, sāriputta, dhanañjāni brāhmaṇo, brahmalokañca upapanno”ti. "
msgstr "“And Sāriputta, the brahmin Dhanañjāni has passed away and been reborn in the Brahmā realm.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "mn97:38.8"
msgid "Dhanañjānisuttaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ sattamaṃ. "
msgstr ""

